    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-08-18T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-08-18T12:00:00-05:00" n="854"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d854">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/8–1853: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Alger</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d854fn1">Repeated to London and Paris for information;
                        passed by the Department of State to the Mission at the United Nations at
                        4:40 p.m., Aug. 18.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brussels</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-08-18T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >August 18, 1953—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>131. Department telegram 161, August 14, and Embassy telegram 127, August 17. In
                    further discussion of Belgian decision withdraw from committee on
                    non-self-governing territories Foreign Office official said this morning that
                    French and <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> Embassies have associated
                    themselves with our representations.</p>
                <p>While Foreign Office has not yet received word from its <gloss target="#t_UN1"
                        >UN</gloss> delegate confirming that notification of withdrawal has been
                    given, Foreign Office official said that Belgian <gloss target="#t_UN1"
                        >UN</gloss> delegate does not possess authority to postpone action. Foreign
                    Office official made personal comment that “strong pressure from Belgium’s best
                    friends” had been fully anticipated by Foreign Office.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Alger</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
